No dosage adjustment is necessary in patients with renal impairment [see
                           Clinical Pharmacology    (12.3)
                           ].

Finasteride pharmacokinetics have not been investigated in patients <18 years of age. Finasteride is not indicated for use in pediatric patients [seeWarnings and Precautions   (5.4)  ,
                           Use in Specific Populations    (8.4)
                           ].
